UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Flipping Bangers
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Rover: Gus and Will set out to buy a Honda-based Rover 800 coupe. At only 650 pounds it seems too good to be true - and when they turn up, they aren't sure whether to proceed. S2 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Jaguar 2+2 E Type: Paul's on a big day out collecting a 1971 Jaguar E-Type and a 1933 Morgan 3-wheeler Supersport but first there's a flock of 300 chickens to negotiate before he can load up. S7 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Subaru Impreza: Dave's in fast car heaven as he picks up a rare Subaru Impreza and an equally powerful Ford Escort RS Cosworth from North Wales. S7 Ep12

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Granada: A rare 1968 Honda N600 car emerges from a lock up in County Durham and Derek's in Scotland to collect an original RAC Bedford van. S7 Ep13

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Nash Metropolitan: Derek collects five beautiful veteran motorbikes from an enthusiast who's still happily riding in his 90s. S7 Ep14

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Ford Capri Consort: A rare 1964 Ford Capri Consul coupe comes up for auction. Paul takes a 1957 Leyland Comet truck for a spin, and Dave admits that high on his wish-list is a Citroen 2CV. S7 Ep15

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Shopping from Home.

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: London to Monte Carlo: Armed with his 1913 guide, Michael Portillo follows the most popular Edwardian route through France, stopping at Paris and the Cote D'Azur along the way. S1 Ep1

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Great Continental Railway Journeys
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Hungary to Austria: Michael Portillo explores the once-great empire of Austria-Hungary. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Bentley S3/Fiesta XR2: Anglophile Derek struggles to get his message across on a rare trip abroad to pick up a Bentley, while a well-restored Ford XR2 sets the auction alight. S2 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Bangers & Cash
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Sunbeam Lotus/Morris Minor Convert: Dave finds a very rare 70s Sunbeam Lotus that has been rotting away in a farmyard for 29 years, while a Morris Minor convertible goes under the hammer. S2 Ep4

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: Secrets & Spies: A Nuclear Game
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Traitors: Spies work behind the scenes as the superpowers enter a new era. Intelligence pushes world leaders towards a more peaceful approach, but a new danger is lurking in the shadows. S1 Ep2

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.title: World War Weird
UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Crossword puzzles in a national newspaper begin to attract the attention of MI5, the answers are code words for the upcoming D-Day operation. Is this the work of a spy? S2 Ep3

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Aston Hall 2: Fiona Bruce presents the show from the grounds of Aston Hall in Birmingham, joined by Benjamin Zephaniah, who shares his passion for unusual banknotes and currency. S44 Ep11

UAndYesterdayPlus1.uk.description: Dyffryn Gardens 2: Fiona and the team are at Dyffryn Gardens near Cardiff, where treasures include a ship's chest from the Windrush, and a clock that runs on air. S44 Ep12
